          <p class="ba-sub">For writers who need immediate visual feedback on sentence complexity and reading level.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Hemingway Editor highlights sentences by complexity — purple for very hard, red for hard, yellow for long. It scores your article by reading grade level. It flags passive voice, adverbs, and unnecessarily complex phrasing. The browser version is free and requires no account. The desktop version ($19.99 one-time) adds basic formatting and export. What it doesn't do: SEO, grammar checking, or publishing. It's a clarity tool for writers who want leaner, more readable copy.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Instant visual feedback on sentence complexity — no account required</h4><p>Paste text into the browser tool and see exactly which sentences need to be simplified.</p></div></li>
